93740-S1E1.name: The Emperor's Peace
93740-S1E1.overview: Gaal Dornick leaves her life in Synnax behind when the galaxy's greatest mathematician, Hari Seldon, invites her to Trantor.

93740-S1E2.name: Preparing to Live
93740-S1E2.overview: The Foundation makes the long journey to Terminus as Gaal and Raych grow closer. The Empire faces a difficult decision.

93740-S1E3.name: The Mathematician's Ghost
93740-S1E3.overview: Brother Dusk reflects on his legacy as he prepares for ascension. The Foundation arrives on Terminus and finds a mysterious object.

58474-S1E1.name: Standing Up in the Milky Way
58474-S1E1.overview: The Ship of the Imagination, unfettered by ordinary limits on speed and size, drawn by the music of cosmic harmonies, can take us anywhere in space and time. It has been idling for more than three decades, and yet it has never been overtaken. Its global legacy remains vibrant. Now, it's time once again to set sail for the stars.

58474-S1E2.name: Some of the Things that Molecules Do
58474-S1E2.overview: Host Neil deGrasse Tyson is on a voyage to explore the relatedness of all living things and the possible evolution of life in the cosmos. Go on a journey to discover how artificial selection turned the wolf into canine breeds and how natural selection sculpted the complex human eye. Later, Tyson visits the grand Hall of Extinction, a monument to all the broken branches on the tree of life. Retrace the story of life on Earth and the unbroken thread that stretches from the first one-celled organisms to human life.

58474-S1E3.name: When Knowledge Conquered Fear
58474-S1E3.overview: There was a time, not so long ago, when natural events could only be understood as gestures of divine displeasure. We will witness the moment that all changed; but first, the Ship of the Imagination is in the brooding, frigid realm of the Oort Cloud, where a trillion comets wait. Our Ship takes us on a hair-raising ride, chasing a single comet through its million-year plunge towards the Sun.

58474-S1E4.name: A Sky Full of Ghosts
58474-S1E4.overview: An exploration of how light, time and gravity combine to distort our perceptions of the universe. We eavesdrop on a series of walks along a beach on summer nights in the year 1809. William Herschel, whose many discoveries include the insight that telescopes are time machines, tells bedtime stories to his young son, John, who will grow up to make some rather profound discoveries of his own.

58474-S1E5.name: Hiding in the Light
58474-S1E5.overview: The Ship of the Imagination travels back in time to reveal 11th century Europe and North Africa during the golden age of Islam, when brilliant physicist Ibn al-Haytham discovered the scientific method and first understood how we see, and how light travels. Later, William Herschel discovers the infrared and the signature hidden in the light of every star, eventually unlocking one of the keys to the cosmos.

58474-S1E6.name: Deeper, Deeper, Deeper Still
58474-S1E6.overview: The Ship of the Imagination ventures on an epic voyage to the bottom of a dewdrop to explore the universe on the smallest scale and observe exotic life forms invisible to the naked eye. Then, host Neil deGrasse Tyson explains the neural network in our brains which determine our sense of smell and memory, and later, he travels deep beneath the surface of the Earth to discover the most mysterious particle we know.

58474-S1E7.name: The Clean Room
58474-S1E7.overview: To determine the true age of the Earth, geochemist Clair Patterson developed the uranium-lead dating method to make an unprecedented discovery – calculating Earth's age of 4.5 billion years. But Patterson's groundbreaking discoveries were just beginning. Patterson made it his mission to draw public attention to the detrimental effects of lead in the environment and dedicated his career to fighting against the petroleum and chemical industry, eventually achieving public health's biggest victory of the 20th century.

58474-S1E8.name: Sisters of the Sun
58474-S1E8.overview: Discover the remarkable story of Annie Jump Cannon and Cecilia Payne, two incredible women who challenged conventional wisdom and uncovered the real-life story of the stars. Cannon led a group of female astronomers in the early 20th century to catalogue the spectral characters of stars, and two decades later, young British beauty Payne joined forces with  Cannon to analyze the data and uncover the chemical compositions of the stars. Later, travel on the Ship of the Imagination to explore the lives and deaths of stars.

58474-S1E9.name: The Lost Worlds of Planet Earth
58474-S1E9.overview: The Ship of the Imagination embarks on a journey through space and time to grasp how the autobiography of the Earth is written in its atoms, its oceans, its continents and all living things. Later, American geologist Marie Tharp creates the first true map of Earth’s ocean floor, and discovers microscopic life that exists deep beneath the ocean.

58474-S1E10.name: The Electric Boy
58474-S1E10.overview: Travel to 19th century England and meet Michael Faraday, a child of poverty who grew up to invent the motor and the generator. His ideas about electricity and discovery of magnetic fields changed the world and paved the way for future scientists to make giant strides in the world of high technology and instantaneous communication.

58474-S1E11.name: The Immortals
58474-S1E11.overview: The Ship of the Imagination travels across the cosmos to discover the possibility of beings that live forever and explain why other civilizations perish. Then, visit the Cosmic Calendar of the Future and contemplate what lies ahead with a hopeful vision.

58474-S1E12.name: The World Set Free
58474-S1E12.overview: The Ship of the Imagination travels to our near neighbor Venus, where we begin our journey to discover the long history of global warming and the greenhouse effect. Later, explore the detrimental effects of climate change and trace the magnitude of our impact on the Earth’s atmosphere. However, with knowledge, technology and science within our grasp, imagine a hopeful future where we dedicate our efforts to taking care of our home, Planet Earth.

58474-S1E13.name: Unafraid of the Dark
58474-S1E13.overview: The Ship of the Imagination makes a final journey to explore one of the biggest mysteries of the universe: dark energy. Meet one of science's greatest unsung heroes, Fritz Zwicky, whose prediction of supernovas paved the way for our larger understanding of dark energy, the unknown force in the universe that overwhelms gravity on the grandest scale. On our final voyage, discover the romantic message embedded in Voyager's Interstellar Golden Record and contemplate the spiritual experience of life on Earth as our cosmic journey concludes with Carl Sagan's unforgettable meditation, The Pale Blue Dot.

248830-S1E1.name: Pilot
248830-S1E1.overview: Pryce is down on his luck when a chance encounter at the driving range sends him on a mission to secure the opportunity of a lifetime.

4629-S1E3.name: The Enemy Within
4629-S1E3.overview: Major Kawalsky is possessed by a Goa'uld, and the SGC must find a way to remove it without killing him.

4629-S1E4.name: Emancipation
4629-S1E4.overview: An alien civilization is forced to reconsider their views on women when Carter rebels against their social customs.

4629-S1E5.name: The Broca Divide
4629-S1E5.overview: Members of SG-1 become infected with an alien virus that turns them into primitive beings. Dr. Fraiser must find a cure to save the team and the alien population from whom it was contracted.

4629-S1E6.name: The First Commandment
4629-S1E6.overview: SG-1 must stop a renegade Stargate commander, who has gone mad and set himself up as a god on an alien planet.

4629-S1E7.name: Cold Lazarus
4629-S1E7.overview: During an off-world assignment, Jack is struck down by energy from a blue crystal... which creates a duplicate of him that returns to Earth in Jack's place.

4629-S1E8.name: The Nox
4629-S1E8.overview: Pressed by the government to acquire new technologies, SG-1 is led to a world inhabited by a seemingly primative race. When Apophis arrives, SG-1 ambush him with disasterous consequences.

4629-S1E9.name: Brief Candle
4629-S1E9.overview: SG-1 discovers a race of attractive people who age extremely rapidly. The situation becomes personal when O'Neill begins to suffer from the same accelerated aging, and must live out the rest of his life on the planet.

4629-S1E10.name: Thor's Hammer
4629-S1E10.overview: Teal'c and O'Neill are transported to an underground cage designed by the Asgard to protect an alien world from the Goa'uld.

4629-S1E11.name: The Torment of Tantalus
4629-S1E11.overview: SG-1 tracks down Catherine Langford's fiancee, who took the first Stargate trip in 1945, and discovers an ancient meeting hall that may hold the secrets of the universe itself.

4629-S1E12.name: Bloodlines
4629-S1E12.overview: Teal'c returns to Chulak to stop his people from implanting his son with a larval Goa'uld.

4629-S1E13.name: Fire and Water
4629-S1E13.overview: Daniel is taken captive by an alien with a hidden agenda, while SG-1 is made to believe he is dead.

4629-S1E14.name: Hathor
4629-S1E14.overview: The banished Goa'uld Hathor is found in an ancient sarcophagus Earth, and takes over the S.G.C. with hopes of raising a new army against the System Lords.

4629-S1E15.name: Singularity
4629-S1E15.overview: A mysterious affliction wipes out the entire population of a planet, plus an SG team -- except for one young girl. Carter befriends her, but learns that she is being used by the Goa'uld.

4629-S1E16.name: Cor-Ai
4629-S1E16.overview: Teal'c must stand trial for a crime committed while he served as first prime of Apophis when a villager on an alien world identifies him as the Jaffa who killed his father.

4629-S1E17.name: Enigma
4629-S1E17.overview: The SG-1 team rescues a group of advanced humans from a planet near destruction, and must find a new home for the refugees before the Pentagon gets their hands on them.

4629-S1E18.name: Solitudes
4629-S1E18.overview: Colonel O'Neill and Captain Carter are separated from Jackson and Teal'c during a Stargate journey, and are trapped on a desolate ice world with no way of escape.

4629-S1E19.name: Tin Man
4629-S1E19.overview: The members of SG-1 arrive on P3X-989 and are knocked unconscious. They wake up and return to Earth only to find that they are not quite themselves.

4629-S1E20.name: There But For the Grace of God
4629-S1E20.overview: An alien artifact transports Daniel to an alternate reality, where he is not a part of the Stargate program and the Goa'uld -- led by Teal'c -- are invading Earth.

4629-S1E21.name: Politics (1)
4629-S1E21.overview: Senator Kinsey arrives at the SGC to investigate the program and determine whether the great drain on the U.S. budget is worthwhile, prompting the team to recall missions from the past year.

4629-S1E22.name: Within the Serpent's Grasp (2)
4629-S1E22.overview: SG-1 escapes through the Stargate before it is shut down, and learns that Daniel's alternate reality vision is true: Apophis is moving to attack Earth from above. The team must stop Apophis and his son, Klorel, who inhabits the body of their friend Skaara.

4629-S2E1.name: The Serpent's Lair (3)
4629-S2E1.overview: With SG-1 trapped on Klorel's ship, it seems that Earth is doomed as the Pyramid Ships prepare to destroy Earth.

4629-S2E2.name: In the Line of Duty
4629-S2E2.overview: Carter is possessed by a Goa'uld who claims to be an enemy of the System Lords.

4629-S2E3.name: Prisoners
4629-S2E3.overview: SG-1 is put on trial and exiled to a prison world, where a woman maintains a strange control over her fellow prisoners.

4629-S2E4.name: The Gamekeeper
4629-S2E4.overview: SG-1 is imprisoned in a virtual reality realm and forced to relive the worst moments of their lives over and over.

4629-S2E5.name: Need
4629-S2E5.overview: Jackson becomes addicted to the effects of a Goa'uld sarcophagus, and falls for the planet's manipulative princess.

4629-S2E6.name: Thor's Chariot
4629-S2E6.overview: SG-1 returns to Cimmeria, and finds that without protection from the Asgard the planet has been invaded by the Goa'uld.

4629-S2E7.name: Message in a Bottle
4629-S2E7.overview: SG-1 discovers an ancient artifact that takes O'Neill and the S.G.C. hostage.

4629-S2E8.name: Family
4629-S2E8.overview: The SG-1 team attempt to rescue Teal'c's son, who has been kidnapped and brainwashed by Apophis. Teal'c learns disturbing news about his wife.

4629-S2E9.name: Secrets
4629-S2E9.overview: Jackson discovers that his wife has returned to Abydos, and is nine months pregnant with the son of Apophis. O'Neill must keep the secret of the Stargate program from being uncovered.

4629-S2E10.name: Bane
4629-S2E10.overview: Teal'c is infected with deadly venom from a giant insect, and begins a terrible transformation. When he escapes the S.G.C., SG-1 must find him before Colonel Maybourne does.

4629-S2E11.name: The Tok'ra (1)
4629-S2E11.overview: SG-1 locates the Tok'ra, a Goa'uld resistance movement who oppose the System Lords, and attempt to form an alliance. Jacob Carter's cancer brings him near death.

4629-S2E12.name: The Tok'ra (2)
4629-S2E12.overview: While SG-1 tries to form an alliance with the Tok'ra, a spy betrays the rebels to the Goa'uld. Jacob Carter finds that the Tok'ra may be his only hope of survival

4629-S2E13.name: Spirits
4629-S2E13.overview: SG-1 finds a planet inhabited by Native American Indians, protected by spirits who are actually advanced alien shapeshifters.

4629-S2E14.name: Touchstone
4629-S2E14.overview: SG-1 is accused of stealing an important weather-controlling device, sending a primative planet into chaos. The team discovers that Earth's second Stargate is being misused.

4629-S2E15.name: The Fifth Race
4629-S2E15.overview: O'Neill becomes the unwilling receptacle for a library of alien knowledge.

4629-S2E16.name: A Matter of Time
4629-S2E16.overview: After gating to a world on the edge of a black hole, the S.G.C. cannot disengage the Stargate. All of Earth becomes endangered by the time-distorting gravity field.

4629-S2E17.name: Holiday
4629-S2E17.overview: SG-1 discovers an elderly man known for developing technology to fight the Goa'uld. Daniel is tricked into switching bodies with the man, Ma'chello, who believes he is "owed" for all the good he has done.

4629-S2E18.name: Serpent's Song
4629-S2E18.overview: Apophis, SG-1's greatest enemy, seeks sanctuary from Sokar and ends up near death in the S.G.C. infirmary.

4629-S2E19.name: One False Step
4629-S2E19.overview: A group of primitive aliens begin to fall deathly ill after SG-1 arrives.

4629-S2E20.name: Show and Tell
4629-S2E20.overview: A young boy arrives through the Stargate, and warns of plot by invisible aliens to kill all of the human race in order to rob the Goa'uld of potential hosts.

4629-S2E21.overview: A cosmic accident causes SG-1 to be sent back 30 years into Earth's past, where they must locate the Stargate and find a way home.

4629-S2E22.name: Out of Mind (1)
4629-S2E22.overview: O'Neill, Carter and Jackson awaken from stasis in what appears to be the S.G.C. -- almost 80 years in the future.

4629-S3E1.name: Into the Fire (2)
4629-S3E1.overview: O'Neill, Carter and Jackson must escape Hathor's clutches, while Teal'c tries to raise a Jaffa army on Chulak. General Hammond must take desperate measures to rescue the team.

4629-S3E2.name: Seth
4629-S3E2.overview: SG-1 must find a renegade Goa'uld who has been hiding on Earth for thousands of years.

4629-S3E3.name: Fair Game
4629-S3E3.overview: The Asgard aid Earth in negotiating a nonagression treaty with the Goa'uld System Lords.

4629-S3E4.name: Legacy
4629-S3E4.overview: When Daniel goes insane, SG-1 must deal with the legacy of Machello's anti-Goa'uld technology.

4629-S3E5.name: Learning Curve
4629-S3E5.overview: SG-1 discovers a planet where children are used to acquire knowledge for the entire population, then discarded.

4629-S3E6.name: Point of View
4629-S3E6.overview: SG-1 must free an alternate reality Earth from a Goa'uld invasion after duplicates of Samantha Carter and Charles Kawalsky come through the quantum mirror.

4629-S3E7.name: Deadman Switch
4629-S3E7.overview: SG-1 is taken captive by an alien bounty hunter with uncertain loyalties.

4629-S3E8.name: Demons
4629-S3E8.overview: SG-1 finds a medieval Christian society terrorized by Sokar and the Unas, and is accused of being possessed by demons.

4629-S3E9.name: Rules of Engagement
4629-S3E9.overview: SG-1 discovers a military camp where young men are trained to impersonate SGC personnel to infiltrate Earth.

4629-S3E10.name: Forever in a Day
4629-S3E10.overview: Jackson deals with the apparent death of his wife, Sha're, at the hands of Teal'c.

4629-S3E11.name: Past and Present
4629-S3E11.overview: SG-1 encounters an entire planet suffering from amnesia.  The planet's leader returns to Earth with SG-1 to find a cure,  but SG-1 suspects she may not be who she appears to be.

4629-S3E12.name: Jolinar's Memories (1)
4629-S3E12.overview: When Major Carter's father Jacob is kidnapped by Sokar, the SG-1 team must infiltrate a prison moon designed to look like hell to rescue him.

4629-S3E13.name: The Devil You Know (2)
4629-S3E13.overview: SG-1 must escape a hellish prison moon, and one of their worst enemies.

4629-S3E14.name: Foothold
4629-S3E14.overview: SG-1 returns from a mission and discovers that metamorphic aliens have taken over the complex.

4629-S3E15.name: Pretense
4629-S3E15.overview: The Tollan put Skaara and Klorel on trial to determine who will control the host body.

4629-S3E16.name: Urgo
4629-S3E16.overview: SG-1 receives alien brain implants that manifest themselves as a bizarre man, who tells them that they would not survive the procedure to remove him.

4629-S3E17.name: A Hundred Days
4629-S3E17.overview: After a meteor strike buries the Stargate, O'Neill finds himself stranded on a planet with no hope of rescue.

4629-S3E18.name: Shades of Grey
4629-S3E18.overview: O'Neill steals technology from the Tollan, and is forced to leave the Stargate program. Maybourne offers an intriguing proposal.

4629-S3E19.name: New Ground
4629-S3E19.overview: The members of SG-1 are imprisoned on a planet and become pawns in a war of ideology.

4629-S3E20.name: Maternal Instinct
4629-S3E20.overview: SG-1 discovers the mystical planet Kheb, and must find the Harcesis child of Apophis and Sha're before Apophis's army does.

4629-S3E21.name: Crystal Skull
4629-S3E21.overview: An alien artifact causes Daniel to disappear, and the team looks for help from his institutionalized grandfather.

4629-S3E22.name: Nemesis (1)
4629-S3E22.overview: SG-1 faces creatures of mass destruction that even the Asgard can't control, and must destroy Thor's infested vessel before the Replicator bugs reach Earth.

4629-S4E1.name: Small Victories (2)
4629-S4E1.overview: O'Neill and Teal'c risk their lives to keep the Replicator bugs from gaining a foothold on Earth, while Carter helps the Asgard fend off a Replicator invasion.

4629-S4E2.name: The Other Side
4629-S4E2.overview: A warring alien race offers to exchange their advanced technology for Earth's help in defeating their enemy.

4629-S4E3.name: Upgrades
4629-S4E3.overview: A Tok'ra archaeologist arrives at the SGC with newly discovered technology, giving the SG-1 team superhuman powers.

4629-S4E4.name: Crossroads
4629-S4E4.overview: Teal'c is reunited with his lost love -- a woman who claims to have found a way to communicate with her symbiote and defeat the Goa'uld.

4629-S4E5.name: Divide and Conquer
4629-S4E5.overview: When a member of the SGC tries to kill a Tok'ra, it is revealed that O'Neill and Carter may be victims of an untraceable form of Goa'uld mind control.

4629-S4E6.name: Window of Opportunity
4629-S4E6.overview: O'Neill and Teal'c are caught in a time loop in the SGC, and must relive the same 10 hours over and over again.

4629-S4E7.name: Watergate
4629-S4E7.overview: The Russians recover a Stargate from the bottom of the ocean, and turn to the SGC for help when their experiments go awry.

4629-S4E8.name: The First Ones
4629-S4E8.overview: Dr. Jackson is taken captive by an Unas while on an archaeological dig. The SGC mounts a rescue operation, but discovers a danger of their own.

4629-S4E9.name: Scorched Earth
4629-S4E9.overview: SG-1 is caught in a conflict between two civilizations trying to colonize the same planet.

4629-S4E10.name: Beneath the Surface
4629-S4E10.overview: The members of SG-1 are used as forced labor in an underground alien facility after their memories are erased by the ruling elite.

4629-S4E11.name: Point of No Return
4629-S4E11.overview: SG-1 investigates a conspiracy theorist who has detailed knowledge of the Stargate program.

4629-S4E12.name: Tangent
4629-S4E12.overview: A test gone wrong leaves Jack and Teal'c marooned in space aboard a damaged prototype attack ship

4629-S4E13.name: The Curse
4629-S4E13.overview: When his former mentor dies, Dr. Jackson returns to his roots -- and discovers an ancient Egyptian artifact containing a Goa'uld parasite.

4629-S4E14.name: The Serpent's Venom
4629-S4E14.overview: SG-1 must stop Apophis and Heru-ur from forming an alliance of their powerful forces, while Teal'c is captured and tortured by the Goa'uld.

4629-S4E15.name: Chain Reaction
4629-S4E15.overview: SG-1 must adjust to a new commanding officer when General Hammond steps down -- but O'Neill discovers foul play behind the general's resignation.

4629-S4E16.overview: Ten years into the future, the former members of SG-1 must send a message into the past to prevent the extinction of the human race.

4629-S4E17.name: Absolute Power
4629-S4E17.overview: Jackson's teammates notice a disturbing change in him when he is reunited with the Harcesis child and given the Goa'uld genetic memory.

4629-S4E18.name: The Light
4629-S4E18.overview: SG-1 finds a deserted Goa'uld palace, where a beautiful device causes suicidal tendencies.

4629-S4E19.name: Prodigy
4629-S4E19.overview: Carter must help keep a promising young cadet from throwing away a future at the SGC. O'Neill and Teal'c encounter a dangerous life form at an offworld research base.

4629-S4E20.name: Entity
4629-S4E20.overview: The SGC is invaded by an alien life force that takes up residence in the base computer system -- and in Major Carter.

4629-S4E21.name: Double Jeopardy
4629-S4E21.overview: SG-1 must rescue an alien world from the Goa'uld -- with help from an unexpected source. Teal'c seeks revenge on the System Lord Cronus for the murder of his father.

4629-S4E22.name: Exodus (1)
4629-S4E22.overview: SG-1 helps to evacuate the Tok'ra to a new base -- but matters are complicated when a spy reveals their location to Apophis. The team attempts a daring plan to take out the Goa'uld's powerful fleet.

4629-S5E1.name: Enemies (2)
4629-S5E1.overview: SG-1 finds themselves stranded in a crippled ship in a distant galaxy -- with Apophis threatening to destroy them. Teal'c is brainwashed and made loyal to Apophis once again.

4629-S5E2.name: Threshold (3)
4629-S5E2.overview: His mind altered by Apophis, Teal'c must undergo a ritual that takes him to the edge of death itself, in order for him to rediscover who he is.

4629-S5E3.name: Ascension
4629-S5E3.overview: An alien being is smitten with Carter and follows her back to Earth. It assumes a human form and pursues a relationship with her.

4629-S5E4.name: The Fifth Man
4629-S5E4.overview: O'Neill and Lieutenant Tyler are ambushed by Goa'uld forces and trapped behind enemy lines -- while the rest of their team discover they don't know who Tyler is.

4629-S5E5.name: Red Sky
4629-S5E5.overview: SG-1 discovers that their recent trip through the Stargate may have inadvertently doomed an entire civilization.

4629-S5E6.name: Rite of Passage
4629-S5E6.overview: Cassandra mysteriously falls ill, sending SG-1 back to her home planet -- where they uncover a dark Goa'uld secret.

4629-S5E7.name: Beast of Burden
4629-S5E7.overview: SG-1 discovers a civilization that uses Unas as slave labor, and attempt to liberate Daniel's friend, Chaka.

4629-S5E8.name: The Tomb
4629-S5E8.overview: SG-1 teams with a Russian unit when one of their Stargate teams goes missing in a mysterious alien ziggurat.

4629-S5E9.name: Between Two Fires
4629-S5E9.overview: The Tollan offer Earth advanced weapons technology, prompting a secret investigation on Tollana -- one that leads to a startling discovery.

4629-S5E10.overview: SG-1 encounters a potential new, technologically advanced ally in the war against the Goa'uld -- though they do not know the Aschen's dark secret.

4629-S5E11.name: Desperate Measures
4629-S5E11.overview: When Carter goes missing, O'Neill teams up with Col. Maybourne again to free her.

guest_stars.character: Nick Marlowe / Colonel Danning / Michael DeLuise
guest_stars.name: Michael DeLuise

guest_stars.character: Raymond Gunne / Dr. Levant / Christian Bocher
guest_stars.name: Christian Bocher

4629-S5E12.name: Wormhole X-Treme!
4629-S5E12.overview: An alien ship approaches Earth, sending SG-1 to an old friend for some answers -- where they discover that Martin Lloyd has created a TV show about the Stargate program.

4629-S5E13.name: Proving Ground
4629-S5E13.overview: SG-1 trains a team of raw cadets, and Colonel O'Neill is forced to take them into a real-life battle situation when he learns of a possible alien incursion at the SGC.

4629-S5E14.name: 48 Hours
4629-S5E14.overview: Disaster strikes the Stargate, trapping Teal'c in transit. SG-1 must turn to Russia -- and to their enemies -- for help.

4629-S5E15.name: Summit (1)
4629-S5E15.overview: The Tok'ra war with the Goa'uld escalates, and the rebel faction sends Daniel Jackson to a secret meeting between the System Lords.

4629-S5E16.name: Last Stand (2)
4629-S5E16.overview: Dr. Jackson's undercover mission to a Goa'uld summit is complicated by the arrival of a surprise guest. The rest of the team face a full-scale invasion of the Tok'ra homeworld.

4629-S5E17.name: Fail Safe
4629-S5E17.overview: Earth finds itself threatened by something even larger than the Goa'uld when the team learns that an asteroid is on a collision course with the planet.

4629-S5E18.name: The Warrior
4629-S5E18.overview: A charismatic Jaffa leader seeks to forge an alliance between Earth and his rebel followers, winning the allegiance of Teal'c and Bra'tac.

4629-S5E19.name: Menace
4629-S5E19.overview: SG-1 encounters a young woman with the ability to control Replicators, and who may hold the key to the salvation of the Asgard.

4629-S5E20.name: The Sentinel
4629-S5E20.overview: SG-1 must turn to a pair of convicted criminals to save a world from annihilation by the Goa'uld.

4629-S5E21.name: Meridian
4629-S5E21.overview: Daniel Jackson is exposed to a lethal dose of radiation while visiting an alien civilization that is building a weapon of mass destruction.

4629-S5E22.name: Revelations
4629-S5E22.overview: SG-1 must come to the rescue of their once-powerful allies when the Goa'uld attack a secret Asgard laboratory.

4629-S6E1.name: Redemption (1)
4629-S6E1.overview: Tragedy reunites Teal'c with his son, who blames him for the death of his mother. O'Neill and Carter launch a risky plan with untested technology when Earth comes under attack by the Goa'uld.

4629-S6E2.name: Redemption (2)
4629-S6E2.overview: Carter must find a way to save Earth from total destruction at the hands of the Goa'uld, who have turned the Stargate into a doomsday bomb. Rya'c joins his father on a mission to destroy the Goa'uld weapon.

4629-S6E3.name: Descent
4629-S6E3.overview: SG-1 boards an abandoned Goa'uld mothership that has mysteriously arrived in Earth's orbit, and must escape the doomed vessel when it crashes into the ocean.

4629-S6E4.name: Frozen
4629-S6E4.overview: SG-1 investigates the discovery of a woman frozen in the ice in Antarctica, who may be a link to the gate builders. A mysterious disease threatens to kill everyone at the research base.

4629-S6E5.name: Nightwalkers
4629-S6E5.overview: Carter, Teal'c and Jonas investigate the death of a scientist with connections to the Goa'uld, and find a small town whose citizens harbor a dark secret.

4629-S6E6.name: Abyss
4629-S6E6.overview: O'Neill is captured and tortured by the Goa'uld, and must rely on an old friend to survive.

4629-S6E7.name: Shadow Play
4629-S6E7.overview: Jonas' people ask Earth for military aid in an impending war with their rival nations, but his former mentor offers another solution: a resistance movement ready for a coup.

4629-S6E8.name: The Other Guys
4629-S6E8.overview: When SG-1 is captured by the Goa'uld, a pair of scientists mount a rescue operation ... whether they're wanted or not.

4629-S6E9.name: Allegiance
4629-S6E9.overview: Tensions rise between the Tok'ra and rebel Jaffa at the S.G.C.'s offworld base when they are attacked by an invisible enemy.

4629-S6E10.name: Cure
4629-S6E10.overview: An alien world offers Earth a medicine with the power to cure any illness -- but the hidden price may be too high to pay.

4629-S6E11.name: Prometheus (1)
4629-S6E11.overview: A news reporter threatens to expose a top-secret military project, but when Carter and Jonas give her a tour of the X-303, they discover that she is a pawn in a much larger plot.

4629-S6E12.name: Unnatural Selection (2)
4629-S6E12.overview: The team is called into battle unexpectedly when the Asgard homeworld is overrun by Replicators -- which have evolved into a startling new form.

4629-S6E13.name: Sight Unseen
4629-S6E13.overview: The team returns to Earth with a piece of technology that allows them to see alien creatures everywhere, and must attempt to contain the problem when it spreads beyond the base.

4629-S6E14.name: Smoke & Mirrors
4629-S6E14.overview: Colonel O'Neill is charged with the murder of Senator Kinsey, and the rest of the team must uncover a conspiracy in order to clear his name.

4629-S6E15.name: Paradise Lost
4629-S6E15.overview: Colonel O'Neill is trapped on an alien planet with Maybourne, and must fight to stay alive as his companion becomes increasingly paranoid.

4629-S6E16.name: Metamorphosis
4629-S6E16.overview: SG-1 attempts to save a planet's inhabitants from Nirrti's genetic experimentation, but find themselves to be her next victims.

4629-S6E17.name: Disclosure
4629-S6E17.overview: General Hammond and the Pentagon reveal the existence of the Stargate to other world governments, and must defend the fact that the program is operated by the United States military.

4629-S6E18.name: Forsaken
4629-S6E18.overview: When the team finds a crashed ship on another planet, their efforts to help the crew effect repairs are hindered by a group of aliens.

4629-S6E19.name: The Changeling
4629-S6E19.overview: A near-death trial causes Teal'c to imagine his life as very different from the one he knows, where he is a normal person living on Earth -- until he can no longer distinguish reality.

4629-S6E20.name: Memento
4629-S6E20.overview: Prometheus is forced to land on an alien world, where the local Stargate is the team's only chance of returning home -- though the local population believe the gate to be a myth.

4629-S6E21.name: Prophecy
4629-S6E21.overview: The team finds an impoverished world enslaved by a Goa'uld underlord, but their plans to free it may be compromised when Jonas experiences unexplained visions of the future.

4629-S6E22.name: Full Circle
4629-S6E22.overview: SG-1 is called to defend the people of Abydos from the Goa'uld once again when they learn that Anubis, in search of a powerful device, is about to attack.

4629-S7E1.name: Fallen (1)
4629-S7E1.overview: While searching for the Lost City of the Ancients on a distant planet, SG-1 is stunned to find Daniel Jackson alive and in human form but stripped of his memory.  O'Neill convinces Daniel to return with them to the SGC, where he is reinstated for a daring mission to destroy Anubis' powerful new super-weapon!

4629-S7E2.name: Homecoming (2)
4629-S7E2.overview: The team returns to Jonas' homeworld when they learn that the Goa'uld are after its naquadria. When Jonas is captured by Anubis, Daniel is his only hope.

4629-S7E3.name: Fragile Balance
4629-S7E3.overview: A teenage boy shows up at the S.G.C. claiming to be Jack O'Neill, sending the team on a mission to uncover his true identity.

4629-S7E4.name: Orpheus
4629-S7E4.overview: After an injury, Teal'c must put aside his self-doubt when SG-1 launches a mission to rescue his son and his mentor from a Jaffa death camp.

4629-S7E5.name: Revisions
4629-S7E5.overview: The team gates to a climate-controlled environment amidst a toxic wasteland, whose people are all linked to a central computer.

4629-S7E6.name: Lifeboat
4629-S7E6.overview: When SG-1 finds a crashed alien space ship, Daniel's mind is taken over by its disembodied passengers.

4629-S7E7.name: Enemy Mine
4629-S7E7.overview: When Earth's attempts to exploit a newly-discovered naquadah mine are thwarted by a tribe of indigenous Unas, SG-1 must turn to an old friend for help.

4629-S7E8.name: Space Race
4629-S7E8.overview: Major Carter joins an alien pilot for a space race, where the winner is awarded a lucrative contract with the planet's most powerful corporation. But the rest of the team discovers that there is more at stake than the finish line.

4629-S7E9.name: Avenger 2.0
4629-S7E9.overview: An S.G.C. scientist creates a computer virus to be used to disable enemy Stargates -- but succeeds in shutting down the entire gate network.

4629-S7E10.name: Birthright
4629-S7E10.overview: The team finds a fugitive colony of Jaffa women, who must prey on other Jaffa to acquire symbiotes.

4629-S7E11.name: Evolution (1)
4629-S7E11.overview: The team investigates an unstoppable new enemy soldier engineered by Anubis. Dr. Jackson leads a team in search of an alien device in Central America, but gets more than he bargained for.

4629-S7E12.name: Evolution (2)
4629-S7E12.overview: O'Neill seeks help from a former comrade to rescue Daniel and Dr. Lee, who have been kidnapped in Central America. Carter, Teal'c and Jacob infiltrate Anubis' super-soldier facility.

4629-S7E13.name: Grace
4629-S7E13.overview: Carter is injured when the Prometheus is attacked by an unknown ship, and awakens to find herself stranded alone in deep space.

4629-S7E14.name: Fallout
4629-S7E14.overview: When the Kelownans discover that a massive underground vein of naquadah is being converted into naquadria, Jonas Quinn seeks help from Earth in avoiding the total destruction of his planet.

4629-S7E15.name: Chimera
4629-S7E15.overview: Daniel is plagued by dreams of his former girlfriend, who has been taken as a Goa'uld host. Samantha Carter begins a romantic relationship with a detective, from whom she must hide her life at Stargate Command.

4629-S7E16.name: Death Knell
4629-S7E16.overview: Earth's secret offworld base is attacked by Anubis' forces, and Major Carter finds herself being hunted by the enemy. General Hammond and Jacob Carter make an unnerving discovery about the Earth-Tok'ra alliance.

4629-S7E17.name: Heroes (1)
4629-S7E17.overview: A film crew arrives to document the work of the S.G.C. for eventual disclosure to the public, but finds that the base's personnel are less than eager to participate.

4629-S7E18.name: Heroes (2)
4629-S7E18.overview: SG-1 is called into action while a film crew is documenting the Stargate program, but the S.G.C. comes under investigation after the mission goes terribly wrong.

4629-S7E19.name: Resurrection
4629-S7E19.overview: SG-1 investigates a secret N.I.D. laboratory, where a ruthless scientist has used cloning technology to create a Goa'uld-human hybrid.

4629-S7E20.name: Inauguration
4629-S7E20.overview: The newly-elected president is debriefed about the Stargate program, and Vice President Kinsey makes a new play for control of the program.

4629-S7E21.name: Lost City (1)
4629-S7E21.overview: O'Neill goes to great lengths to keep the Ancients' knowledge from falling into Goa'uld hands when the team discovers a second repository. The President replaces General Hammond with a civilian diplomat.

4629-S7E22.name: Lost City (2)
4629-S7E22.overview: Anubis begins a systematic assault on Earth, and the planet's only hope of salvation depends on whether SG-1 can find the Ancients' mythical Lost City.

4629-S8E1.name: New Order (1)
4629-S8E1.overview: Carter and Teal'c go in search of the Asgard to try and save Colonel O'Neill, but discover that the Asgard's enemy has returned with a vengeance. The System Lords seek an alliance with Earth against a common enemy.

4629-S8E2.name: New Order (2)
4629-S8E2.overview: While the Goa'uld threaten to attack Earth, SG-1 and the Asgard make a last, desperate stand against the Replicators, which have captured Major Carter and invaded the last outpost of the Asgard civilization.

4629-S8E3.name: Lockdown
4629-S8E3.overview: The S.G.C. is put under quarantine after a mysterious infection leaves a Russian officer in the infirmary -- but the disease may not be a disease at all.

4629-S8E4.name: Zero Hour
4629-S8E4.overview: General O'Neill tries to settle into his new job, but faces never-ending crises - including the capture of SG-1 by the Goa'uld.

4629-S8E5.name: Icon
4629-S8E5.overview: Daniel is stranded on another planet after the team's arrival on an alien world sparks a violent civil war.

4629-S8E6.name: Avatar
4629-S8E6.overview: Teal'c is trapped in a virtual reality simulation, in which he must defend the base from a Goa'uld super-soldier incursion.

4629-S8E7.name: Affinity
4629-S8E7.overview: Teal'c becomes the chief suspect in a murder investigation after he moves into an apartment off-base. Carter considers her future with Pete.

4629-S8E8.name: Covenant
4629-S8E8.overview: A businessman threatens to expose the secrets of alien life to the world, forcing Stargate Command to bring him into the loop.

4629-S8E9.name: Sacrifices
4629-S8E9.overview: The impending wedding of his son is the least of Teal'c's worries when the Hak'tyl plan an uprising against the Goa'uld Moloc, driving a wedge between Teal'c and Ishta.

4629-S8E10.name: Endgame
4629-S8E10.overview: The Stargate is stolen, leading SG-1 to discover that the Trust has taken control of an advanced ship in orbit. Teal'c investigates a series of wide-spread Jaffa deaths.

4629-S8E11.name: Gemini
4629-S8E11.overview: A duplicate of Colonel Carter seeks help from Stargate Command in defeating the Replicator Fifth, who she claims has found a way to counter the Asgard's new weapon.

4629-S8E12.name: Prometheus Unbound
4629-S8E12.overview: After the Prometheus responds to a distress call from a Goa'uld ship, Daniel Jackson finds himself a captive when Earth's ship is stolen.

4629-S8E13.name: It's Good to Be King
4629-S8E13.overview: SG-1 comes to the aid of a world about to be invaded by the Goa'uld, only to discover that the local king is Earth's Harry Maybourne.

4629-S8E14.name: Full Alert
4629-S8E14.overview: Relations between the U.S. and Russia are strained when Russian military leaders claim that the U.S. government has been compromised by the Goa'uld.

4629-S8E15.name: Citizen Joe
4629-S8E15.overview: Jack is confronted in his home by an irate barber...who claims to know everything about the Stargate project and SG-1.

4629-S8E16.name: Reckoning (1)
4629-S8E16.overview: The Replicators begin a systematic attack of the Goa'uld, forcing Baal to come to Earth for help. The Jaffa Resistance risk their entire movement in an attempt to retake a holy city in Baal's domain.

4629-S8E17.name: Reckoning (2)
4629-S8E17.overview: The fate of the galaxy hangs in the balance as Sam and Jacob search for the only weapon capable of stopping the Replicator onslaught. O'Neill leads a defense of the S.G.C., while Daniel squares off against Replicator Carter.

4629-S8E18.name: Threads
4629-S8E18.overview: While Daniel finds himself in a mysterious diner suspended between death and ascension, Jacob's fate takes an unexpected turn, Jack and Sam consider their romantic lives, and Anubis unleashes his plan for galactic destruction.

4629-S8E19.name: Moebius (1)
4629-S8E19.overview: SG-1 travels back in time in a daring plan to steal a piece of Ancient technology from Ra, the powerful Goa'uld who ruled in ancient Egypt.

4629-S8E20.name: Moebius (2)
4629-S8E20.overview: With the timeline changed by SG-1's actions in the distant past, an alternate version of SG-1 must use the newly-discovered time ship to set things right.

2290-S1E3.name: Hide and Seek
2290-S1E3.overview: The Atlantis base is threatened when the team discovers that an alien entity is in the city. McKay's experiment with alien technology goes awry.

2290-S1E4.name: Thirty Eight Minutes
2290-S1E4.overview: The team finds themselves in mortal danger when their Puddle Jumper ship becomes lodged in the Stargate.

2290-S1E5.name: Suspicion
2290-S1E5.overview: After a series of run-ins with the Wraith, the team begins to suspect their Athosian allies of having a spy in their midst.

2290-S1E6.name: Childhood's End
2290-S1E6.overview: Sheppard and the team visit a world where no one is over 24 years old -- because of a ritual suicide practice they believe keeps the Wraith at bay.

2290-S1E7.name: Poisoning the Well
2290-S1E7.overview: The team finds a world whose people are on the brink of a discovery that may make them immune to the Wraith feeding.

2290-S1E8.name: Underground
2290-S1E8.overview: Efforts to open trade relations with a species called the Genii turn sour when the team discovers their new "allies" have ulterior motives.

2290-S1E9.name: Home
2290-S1E9.overview: McKay's efforts to harness the energy of an alien planet's atmosphere allows for a return trip to Earth -- but the team may not be able to return to Atlantis.

2290-S1E10.name: The Storm (1)
2290-S1E10.overview: When a massive storm threatens the city, Atlantis is evacuated -- only to be taken over by the team's newest enemy.

2290-S1E11.name: The Eye (2)
2290-S1E11.overview: Major Sheppard plays a dangerous game of cat and mouse with soldiers who have seized control of Atlantis and have taken Weir and McKay hostage.

2290-S1E12.name: The Defiant One
2290-S1E12.overview: Sheppard's team investigates a downed Wraith ship, and find themselves stuck on a planet with a lone Wraith survivor.

2290-S1E13.name: Hot Zone
2290-S1E13.overview: Nearly a third of Atlantis's residents are infected with a deadly virus that causes hallucinations and death, forcing a lockdown of the city.

2290-S1E14.name: Sanctuary
2290-S1E14.overview: The team finds a paradise world that would make an ideal sanctuary for those fleeing from the Wraith, but the local inhabitants believe their goddess will not permit it.

2290-S1E15.name: Before I Sleep
2290-S1E15.overview: A woman is found in suspended animation in Atlantis, and the team is shocked to see that it is Dr. Weir herself, who tells them of her trip 10,000 years into the city's past.

2290-S1E16.name: The Brotherhood
2290-S1E16.overview: The team searches for a valuable Zero Point Module rumored to be hidden on the planet Dagan -- but their new allies have motives of their own.

2290-S1E17.name: Letters From Pegasus
2290-S1E17.overview: With a brief opportunity to send a data transmission to Earth, members of the Atlantis expedition compose video messages home to their loved ones.

2290-S1E18.name: The Gift
2290-S1E18.overview: Plagued by terrifying nightmares, Teyla begins to recall a time when she and her father were captured by the Wraith and subjected to disturbing experiments.

2290-S1E19.name: The Siege (1)
2290-S1E19.overview: With a group of Wraith hive ships on the way to Atlantis, the team searches for a place to flee and a way to destroy the city. McKay leads a team to try and activate the Ancients' orbital weapons platform.

2290-S1E20.name: The Siege (2)
2290-S1E20.overview: All hope seems lost, until Colonel Everett arrives suddenly from Earth. He is determined to defend the city until the arrival of a ZPM, brought by a new ship.

2290-S2E1.name: The Siege (3)
2290-S2E1.overview: The Daedalus arrives to defend Atlantis from the Wraith onslaught, but it may not be enough when the team discovers that an even larger armada is on the way.

2290-S2E2.name: The Intruder
2290-S2E2.overview: The Daedalus is infected by a Wraith computer virus, while members of the expedition hope to return to Earth.

2290-S2E3.name: Runner
2290-S2E3.overview: Sheppard and his team attempt to locate Lieutenant Ford, only to find themselves captives of a former soldier who is being hunted by the Wraith.

2290-S2E4.name: Duet
2290-S2E4.overview: A run-in with a Wraith Dart leaves the consciousness of a precocious Atlantis security officer trapped in Dr. McKay's mind.

2290-S2E5.name: Condemned
2290-S2E5.overview: The Atlantis team finds a culture that lives in relative safety from the Wraith, because they hand over their criminals to the Wraith -- and crash-land in the volatile penal colony.

2290-S2E6.name: Trinity
2290-S2E6.overview: McKay puts the team at risk when he tries to perfect unfinished Ancient technology that wiped out a civilization. Ronon Dex discovers that he is not the lone survivor from his world.

2290-S2E7.name: Instinct
2290-S2E7.overview: The team discovers a young Wraith girl who has been raised by a human, and is in hiding from the people of her human village in fear of her life.

2290-S2E8.name: Conversion
2290-S2E8.overview: Colonel Sheppard begins to undergo a disturbing physical transformation after being exposed to Beckett's anti-Wraith drug.

2290-S2E9.name: Aurora
2290-S2E9.overview: When the team finds an Ancient warship adrift on the edge of the galaxy, its crew still alive, Colonel Sheppard enters their virtual reality stasis to communicate with them.

2290-S2E10.name: The Lost Boys (1)
2290-S2E10.overview: The team is captured by the missing Lieutenant Ford, who is now leading a group of young men who are taking the Wraith enzyme -- and who wants the team's help in a suicide attack against a hive ship.

2290-S2E11.name: The Hive (2)
2290-S2E11.overview: Colonel Sheppard and his team find themselves prisoners of the Wraith following Ford's attack on a hive ship. Dr. McKay goes to great lengths to help them.

2290-S2E12.name: Epiphany
2290-S2E12.overview: Sheppard finds himself on a planet where time passes more rapidly, with no way to contact his team or return to Atlantis.

2290-S2E13.name: Critical Mass
2290-S2E13.overview: When an operative of the Trust plants a bomb in Atlantis, the team must find a spy within their own ranks before the Wraith arrive and discover the city.

2290-S2E14.name: Grace Under Pressure
2290-S2E14.overview: When Dr. McKay is trapped underwater in a sinking Puddle Jumper, his only chance for survival may be an hallucination of Samantha Carter.

2290-S2E15.name: The Tower
2290-S2E15.overview: The team finds a world that possesses Ancient defense technology, where Colonel Sheppard finds himself a pawn in the rivalry between the heirs to the throne.

2290-S2E16.name: The Long Goodbye
2290-S2E16.overview: The team discovers two pods that contain the minds of alien beings, who take control of Weir and Sheppard's bodies to continue their personal war.

2290-S2E17.name: Coup D'etat
2290-S2E17.overview: After a team from Atlantis goes missing, the expedition finds itself in the middle of a Genii coup.

2290-S2E18.name: Michael
2290-S2E18.overview: An amnesiac young Lieutenant in Atlantis suffers from disturbing nightmares that he is a Wraith, only to make a shocking discovery about himself.

2290-S2E19.name: Inferno
2290-S2E19.overview: Sheppard's team meets a civilization about to be destroyed by a super-volcano, and is trapped there when the Stargate is destroyed during the evacuation.

2290-S2E20.name: Allies (1)
2290-S2E20.overview: Michael and his Wraith faction arrive at Atlantis to propose an alliance, hoping to use the retrovirus to transform their Wraith enemies into prey.

2290-S3E1.name: No Man's Land (2)
2290-S3E1.overview: The team desperately attempts to stop two Wraith hive ships from reaching Earth. Sheppard must rely on an old foe to rescue McKay and Ronon.

2290-S3E2.name: Misbegotten (3)
2290-S3E2.overview: The Atlantis team must decide the fate of a colony of Wraith they have turned into humans. Dr. Weir must defend her leadership when she is evaluated by the I.O.A.

2290-S3E3.name: Irresistible
2290-S3E3.overview: Sheppard's team meets an obnoxious man who is adored by all thanks to a secret that he carries -- and who has an unexpected effect on them.

2290-S3E4.name: Sateda
2290-S3E4.overview: Ronon Dex is captured by the Wraith and returned to his homeworld, where he is haunted by his past as he is forced to once again become their prey.

2290-S3E5.name: Progeny
2290-S3E5.overview: Weir and the team visit an advanced civilization that split off from the Lanteans thousands of years ago, but discover that they may not have left Atlantis in peace.

2290-S3E6.name: The Real World
2290-S3E6.overview: Elizabeth Weir wakes up in a mental institution, where she is told that the expedition to Atlantis and the Stargate are figments of her imagination.

2290-S3E7.name: Common Ground
2290-S3E7.overview: Colonel Sheppard finds himself the prisoner of a Genii commander, along with a desperately hungry Wraith who has been separated from his hive.

2290-S3E8.name: McKay and Mrs. Miller
2290-S3E8.overview: Rodney McKay is reunited with his estranged sister back on Earth, who has given up a brilliant career as a scientist to raise a family.

2290-S3E9.name: Phantoms
2290-S3E9.overview: Sheppard and Ronon are influenced by a mind-altering device created by the Wraith while on a mission to rescue a lost team.

2290-S3E10.name: The Return (1)
2290-S3E10.overview: The Atlantis expedition is stunned to learn that a ship full of Ancients is returning to reclaim their lost city.

2290-S3E11.name: The Return (2)
2290-S3E11.overview: The Atlantis team goes against orders to try and save Atlantis from Replicator control -- and to rescue General O'Neill and Richard Woolsey, who are trapped in the occupied city.

2290-S3E12.name: Echoes
2290-S3E12.overview: The inhabitants of Atlantis begin to suffer ill effects when the planet's whale population begins migrating to the island city, bringing an unexpected harbinger of doom.

2290-S3E13.name: Irresponsible
2290-S3E13.overview: The team finds Lucius Lavin manipulating the people of another hapless planet, using Ancient technology to pose as an invincible hero.

2290-S3E14.name: Tao of Rodney
2290-S3E14.overview: After an Ancient device gives Rodney superhuman powers, his enhanced brilliance is checked only by his impending death -- unless he can learn how to ascend.

2290-S3E15.name: The Game
2290-S3E15.overview: Sheppard and McKay discover that their competitive video game has been controlling a planet of real people, who now stand on the brink of war.

2290-S3E16.name: The Ark
2290-S3E16.overview: The team discovers the last of a civilization in suspended animation, whose survival is at risk when their station is critically damaged.

2290-S3E17.name: Sunday
2290-S3E17.overview: The team tries to relax during a mandatory day off, until an explosion leaves three people dead -- and reveals that one scientist is a walking time bomb.

2290-S3E18.name: Submersion
2290-S3E18.overview: The team discovers an Ancient drilling station deep beneath the surface of the ocean, only to find that a Wraith queen is still alive there.

2290-S3E19.name: Vengeance
2290-S3E19.overview: The Atlantis team investigates the disappearance of one of their allies, only to find an old enemy engineering a race of powerful monsters.

2290-S3E20.name: First Strike (1)
2290-S3E20.overview: An unstoppable energy weapon leaves Atlantis under siege after Earth launches a preemptive attack against a very powerful enemy's homeworld.

2290-S4E1.name: Adrift (2)
2290-S4E1.overview: Floating in deep space with the city's protective shield failing, the team must do all they can to keep Atlantis alive. A radical injury threatens Dr. Weir's life.

2290-S4E2.name: Lifeline (3)
2290-S4E2.overview: Colonel Sheppard and his team embark on a risky mission to steal a Z.P.M. power module from the Replicators -- but must rely on a compromised Dr. Weir to succeed.

2290-S4E3.name: Reunion
2290-S4E3.overview: When a group of Ronon's people enlist the team's help in raiding a Wraith weapons facility, Ronon reconsiders whether his future lies in Atlantis or with his friends.

2290-S4E4.name: Doppelganger
2290-S4E4.overview: During an off-world mission Colonel Sheppard unknowingly becomes host to an alien entity, which infects others in Atlantis and afflicts them with terrifying nightmares.

2290-S4E5.name: Travelers
2290-S4E5.overview: Colonel Sheppard is captured by the inhabitants of a generational ship and their beautiful leader, who wish to use his ability to use Ancient technology for their own ends.

2290-S4E6.name: Tabula Rasa
2290-S4E6.overview: When a virus causes amnesia in everyone except Teyla and Ronon, the Atlantis team must work together to find a cure before their memories fade entirely.

2290-S4E7.name: Missing
2290-S4E7.overview: During a visit to New Athos, Teyla and Dr. Keller find themselves on the run from a primitive tribe of warriors.

2290-S4E8.name: The Seer
2290-S4E8.overview: The team meets a man with extraordinary prophetic abilities, who gives them a dark prediction about Atlantis's future. The Wraith seek a new alliance with Atlantis in their war with the Replicators.

2290-S4E9.name: Miller's Crossing
2290-S4E9.overview: Rodney McKay goes in search of his sister on Earth after she is kidnapped by the head of a powerful corporation.

2290-S4E10.name: This Mortal Coil (1)
2290-S4E10.overview: A mysterious drone crashes into Atlantis, indicating that the Replicators may have found the city. But when Elizabeth Weir appears, the team realizes that the probe is just a part of a bigger mystery.

2290-S4E11.name: Be All My Sins Remember'd (2)
2290-S4E11.overview: With a plan to potentially extinguish the Replicator threat, the Atlantis team must seek an alliance with a fleet of Wraith ships.

2290-S4E12.name: Spoils of War
2290-S4E12.overview: The team finds their former Wraith ally's hive ship drifting in space, which leads them to a secret project that could turn the tide of a civil war.

2290-S4E13.name: Quarantine
2290-S4E13.overview: An automated lockdown traps Atlantis personnel in various parts of the city, each of them hoping the others will come to their rescue.

2290-S4E14.name: Harmony
2290-S4E14.overview: Colonel Sheppard and Dr. McKay must protect a child princess on a pilgrimage before she can become queen, and learn that she has dangerous enemies threatening her life.

2290-S4E15.name: Outcast
2290-S4E15.overview: While on personal leave on Earth, Sheppard and Ronon learn that scientists have engineered a human-form Replicator -- who is now on the loose.

2290-S4E16.name: Trio
2290-S4E16.overview: McKay, Carter, and Keller are trapped in an underground chamber while on an off-world mission, with no apparent means of escape.

2290-S4E17.name: Midway
2290-S4E17.overview: Teal'c visits Atlantis to counsel a headstrong Ronon, who is up for review by the I.O.A. But the two must work together when the Wraith invade the Midway space station in order to reach Earth.

2290-S4E18.name: The Kindred (1)
2290-S4E18.overview: As a mysterious new illness sweeps through the Pegasus Galaxy, Teyla is convinced by a vision that the father of her child is trying to communicate with her.

2290-S4E19.name: The Kindred (2)
2290-S4E19.overview: The team is shocked when an old friend, believed to be dead, miraculously returns to them. Teyla plans an escape from Michael's captivity.

2290-S4E20.name: The Last Man (1)
2290-S4E20.overview: Sheppard returns to Atlantis after a mission and finds the city abandoned, all systems dead -- and instead of ocean, sand dunes as far as the eye can see.

2290-S5E1.name: Search and Rescue (2)
2290-S5E1.overview: Lt. Colonel John Sheppard and his team are trapped under the rubble of Michael's facility in order to rescue Teyla Emmagan. As Colonel Samantha Carter launches a team to rescue the rescuers, little do they know that Michael Kenmore is also searching the planet for the survivors.

2290-S5E2.name: The Seed
2290-S5E2.overview: When a mysterious alien organism takes Dr. Jennifer Keller as its host, the newly revived Dr. Carson Beckett and the crew desperately search for a serum to save her from the evolving intruder before it can infiltrate Atlantis. In the meantime, Richard Woolsey officially joins the team, having been chosen as Colonel Samantha Carter's replacement to lead the Atlantis expedition.

2290-S5E3.name: Broken Ties
2290-S5E3.overview: Ronon Dex is captured by Tyre, who wants to hand him to the Wraith in order to maintain his role in their circle. However, when the deal turns sour, and Tyre is left for dead, the Atlantis expedition persuade him to take back their friend. Meanwhile, The Wraith turn Ronon into a Wraith worshipper.

2290-S5E4.name: The Daedalus Variations
2290-S5E4.overview: The Atlantis expedition mysteriously finds the Daedalus, abandoned and drifting in space. When Lt. Colonel John Sheppard's team come to investigate, the ship mysteriously disappears. They soon discover that the ship is actually an alternate Daedalus from a Alternate reality, and the team must find a way back to their Universe or risk being stranded forever in an unfamiliar reality.

2290-S5E5.name: Ghost in the Machine
2290-S5E5.overview: While on a mission, Lt. Colonel John Sheppard's team inadvertently brings a mysterious entity to Atlantis. They soon learn that the entity is nothing more than Dr. Elizabeth Weir, who was thought to have been killed after her capture by the Asurans.

2290-S5E6.name: The Shrine
2290-S5E6.overview: Dr. Rodney McKay is infected with the Pegasus equivalent of Alzheimer's disease, known as Second Childhood, a common illness among the elderly in the galaxy. The only way to save him is a shrine on Talus. The downside is that it has turned into a Wraith outpost.

2290-S5E7.name: Whispers
2290-S5E7.overview: Dr. Carson Beckett is called in to help a team investigating a lab that once belonged to Michael Kenmore. But soon, they realize that a group of experiments that even Michael couldn't control are hellbent on killing the team.

2290-S5E8.name: The Queen
2290-S5E8.overview: The Atlantis expedition has a plan to remove the Wraith's dependence on feeding to use an experimental gene therapy from Michael's database. However, in order to convince the Primary, the Wraith leader, Teyla Emmagan must pose as a Hive Queen.

2290-S5E9.name: Tracker
2290-S5E9.overview: Dr. Jennifer Keller is kidnapped by a runner named Kiryk. While Dr. Rodney McKay and Ronon Dex tracks them, Kiryk takes Keller to a seriously injured young girl. She must do it fast, since the Wraith have found him, and are hunting them down.

2290-S5E10.name: First Contact (1)
2290-S5E10.overview: Dr. Daniel Jackson arrives in Atlantis to investigate a hidden lab left behind by the rogue Ancient scientist Janus. Their discovery has attracted the attention of a mysterious group of aliens, who infiltrate the city. Meanwhile, "Todd" and a delegation arrive on the Daedalus to bring forward Dr. Jennifer Keller's gene therapy.

2290-S5E11.name: The Lost Tribe (2)
2290-S5E11.overview: As Dr. Rodney McKay and Dr. Daniel Jackson is held prisoner by the Vanir, they make a startling discovery about who they really are. Meanwhile, "Todd" and his Wraith hijack the Daedalus to find and destroy those who activated the Attero device. The Travelers arrive and Lt. Colonel John Sheppard must help them get to the planet before "Todd" uncovers a way to discover the device for good, even if it means sacrificing McKay and Jackson's lives to do so.

2290-S5E12.name: Outsiders
2290-S5E12.overview: Dr. Carson Beckett, now a traveling doctor in Pegasus comes across a planet, where some of the villagers are refugees from Balar, a planet infected with the Hoffan drug, and destroyed by the Wraith. However, the Wraith arrive on the planet and gives the village an ultimatum, hand over the Balarians, or face destruction of the entire civilization.

2290-S5E13.name: Inquisition
2290-S5E13.overview: Lt. Colonel John Sheppard's team is invited by the Coalition of Planets in order to form an alliance. However, the team is misled and is faced to stand trial, for their alleged crimes against the Pegasus galaxy. Their best chance of freedom, is the experiences of Richard Woolsey.

2290-S5E14.name: The Prodigal
2290-S5E14.overview: Michael Kenmore has infiltrated Atlantis with an army of his Hybrids, and closes off Stargate Operations and the surrounded levels to prevent anyone from taking it back. His plan; take Teyla Emmagan and her child to perfect his Hybrids, and to destroy the base when they're done. Meanwhile, Lt. Colonel John Sheppard, Dr. Rodney McKay and a team try to take back the city before Michael leaves with what he wants.

2290-S5E15.name: Remnants
2290-S5E15.overview: While being evaluated by the International Oversight Advisory, Richard Woolsey meets a beautiful scientist new to Atlantis, who is not what she appears. Meanwhile, Lt. Colonel John Sheppard is captured and tortured by an enemy he thought he'd killed several years ago: his sworn enemy, Genii Commander Acastus Kolya.

2290-S5E16.name: Brain Storm
2290-S5E16.overview: Dr. Rodney McKay reluctantly returns to Earth to witness the triumph of his rival Dr. Malcolm Tunney, but must help shut down a deadly weather device when the new technology goes horribly awry.

2290-S5E17.name: Infection
2290-S5E17.overview: After a Wraith Hive Ship shows up over Atlantis transmitting a distress call, Lt. Colonel John Sheppard's team discovers that its crew has been stricken with a disease they helped create.

2290-S5E18.name: Identity
2290-S5E18.overview: Dr. Jennifer Keller's body is inadvertently taken over by a cunning thief, Neeva Casol. While Neeva tries to escape Atlantis, Keller finds herself imprisoned with a death sentence on another planet, forcing the team into a race against time to return Keller to her original body before she is put to death.

2290-S5E19.name: Vegas
2290-S5E19.overview: In the city of Las Vegas in an alternate reality, police Detective John Sheppard investigates a series of bizarre murders where each body appears to have desiccated. He is soon called to Area 51, where Dr. Rodney McKay explains the situation.

2290-S5E20.name: Enemy at the Gate
2290-S5E20.overview: "Todd" informs the Atlantis expedition that a rogue group of Wraith has acquired several Zero Point Modules to power a Super-hive, and wants it destroyed. However, after the Daedalus is disabled, they learn that the ship is heading straight for Earth, and they must stop it before it gets there.
